===Etymology===
Medieval Latin, from {{term|Baioarii|lang=la}} 'Bavarians', from Late Latin {{term|Bojuvarii|lang=la}}, literally, 'Boii settlers', compound of {{etyl|cel-gau}} {{term||Boii}} 'the Boii tribe' and {{proto|Germanic|warjaz}} 'settler' (cf. Old Norse {{term|verjar|lang=non}} 'defender, settler'), from Proto Indo-European (cf. Welsh {{term|gwerin|lang=cy}} 'crowd', Sanskrit {{term||vṛndám}} 'group, troop, crowd'). This name was adopted by the Marcomanni after defeating the Boii and settling [[Bohemia]] and parts of Bavaria.

